name: Dan Sullivan

text: Mr. President, the people who sent us here still have big dreams and big hopes. Let’s help those dreams grow and their hopes flourish.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: Despite challenges, despite big-govt’s creep into our lives, despite armed EPA agents, we continue to live in greatest country in the world.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: I believe our government should be helping, not hindering, these efforts.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: And I think most of us can agree that we must unleash the country’s enormous economic potential once again.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: We want a government that holds dear what our fathers knew – that all powers are derived from the consent of the governed.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: We want to continue to live in the best country in the world, a country of unlimited opportunity, a country of Alaska-sized dreams.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: We want our children to be safe and secure and we want the same for our neighbor.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: We want to be strong here at home which will help us be respected once again by our allies and feared by our adversaries.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: We all want the very best for the people we represent and the states we speak for.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: And finally we must challenge the conventional wisdom that the federal government’s power &  intrusiveness should always be expanding
name: Dan Sullivan

text: Fourth: while I believe in a limited fed. govt, we must recognize where the fed. govt DOES have responsibilities -- like protecting our Vets
name: Dan Sullivan

text: Third: we must get back to the rule of law.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: Second, we need more, not less, access to our federal lands. As Americans, these are OUR lands – not the @Interior or @BLMNational
name: Dan Sullivan

text: Let me suggest a few ideas: First – We MUST stop delaying economic projects that benefit our citizens.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: We must work to once again unleash the great potential that is Alaska and America & we must work to reinvigorate faith in the American dream
name: Dan Sullivan

text: Congress has a job to do. We must work to address the anxiety and frustration of the people we serve.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: What the American people are telling us, is that they want a federal government that helps ignite their hope, not smother it.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: Our citizens are telling us that their government has gone well beyond deriving its powers from the consent of the governed.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: And judging from what Americans are telling us, the reach of the federal government has exceeded its limits.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: Yes, we have major challenges like all states. But in Alaska, we still have hope, we still dream big dreams. TAPS helps fuel these dreams.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: I’m standing in support of what has defined this country for centuries: The idea of the American dream.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: In supporting Keystone, I’m  standing for a larger principle. The ideal that the fed. govt should be a partner in progress. Not an obstacle.
name: Dan Sullivan

text: Today I stand in support of Keystone. As an Alaskan I feel it’s important to talk about this bill & the importance of energy infrastructure
name: Dan Sullivan
